Installation steps : -

creatre aws EC2 instance with t2.medium server have 4 GB RAM is must and open 9000 port for the server
  {2GB for sonarqube running and Swap memory 1GB RAM }
Open server and change to root user
  " sudo -s "
need to update the dependices in the linux server by using cmd " yum update "
Install java in linux " sudo yum install java-1.8.0 -y "
Change directory to opt " cd /opt/ .
Download the sonarqube community version by using the command " wget https://binaries.sonarsource.com/Distribution/sonarqube/sonarqube-7.6.zip "
unzip the sonarqube-7.6.zip file and rename it to sonar directory
add user in linux server like sonar " useradd sonar " and change ownership to sonar for sonar directory " chown -R sonar:sonar /opt/sonarqube " .
  " useradd -c "Sonar System User" -d /opt/sonar76 -g sonar -s /bin/bash sonar "
switch to sonar user and come to the path  cd /opt/sonar76/sonarqube-7.6/bin/linux-x86-64/ directory.
 start the sonarqube by using cmd " ./sonar.sh start " and check the status " ./sonar.sh status"
 then open chrome browser and copy the IP address of EC2 instance with port number enter and it will open the GUI of sonar qube
User name and password both are " admin & admin "
